keyFacts: Jeffrey E. Epstein, as president of Laurel Inc., transferred property (El Bravo Park Lots 39 and 40) to Bliss Inc., a Church Religious Organization, for $200.
The transaction occurred on March 9, 2019, but was not recorded until October 23, 2020, in Palm Beach County, Florida.
The document is a formal Warranty Deed, indicating Epstein's corporate role in a real estate transaction involving a religious organization.
The property transfer is for a nominal sum ($200), which may suggest a non-market transaction such as a gift or internal transfer.
